---
import DocPage from "../../../components/DocPage.astro";
const cb =
  "bg-background-dark p-3 border-l-2 border-border text-foreground-dark text-xs mb-6 overflow-x-auto";
---

<DocPage title="Mode Switching">
  <h1>Mode Switching</h1>

  <p>
    Shannon has two modes — press <strong>Shift+Tab</strong> to toggle between them:
  </p>

  <p class="my-4 text-center text-base">
    <span class="text-success font-bold">nu</span>
    <span class="text-muted">↔</span>
    <span class="text-accent font-bold">bash</span>
  </p>

  <h2>Switching in Action</h2>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-success">[nu]</span> ~/project &gt; <span class="text-primary">ls</span> | <span class="text-primary">where</span> size &gt; 1mb
<span class="text-muted">...</span>
<span class="text-success">[nu]</span> ~/project &gt; <span class="text-secondary">&lt;Shift+Tab&gt;</span>

<span class="text-accent">[bash]</span> ~/project &gt; <span class="text-primary">echo</span> hello &amp;&amp; <span class="text-primary">echo</span> world
<span class="text-muted">hello</span>
<span class="text-muted">world</span>
<span class="text-accent">[bash]</span> ~/project &gt; <span class="text-secondary">&lt;Shift+Tab&gt;</span>

<span class="text-success">[nu]</span> ~/project &gt;</code></pre>

  <p>The prompt updates immediately to show the active mode.</p>

  <h2>What Carries Over</h2>

  <p>When you switch modes, these are preserved:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Environment variables</strong> —
      <code class="text-secondary">export FOO=bar</code> in bash is visible as
      <code class="text-secondary">$env.FOO</code> in nushell
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Working directory</strong> —
      <code class="text-secondary">cd /tmp</code> in bash means you're in
      <code class="text-secondary">/tmp</code> when you switch to nushell
    </li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    Environment variables are converted automatically between nushell's typed
    values and bash strings using <code class="text-secondary"
      >ENV_CONVERSIONS</code
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>What Doesn't Carry Over</h2>

  <p>Shell-internal data stays within its mode:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Nushell variables (<code class="text-secondary">let x = 5</code>) don't
      exist in bash
    </li>
    <li>Bash local variables and aliases don't exist in nushell</li>
    <li>Only exported environment variables cross the boundary</li>
  </ul>
</DocPage>
